From: Benjamin Walsh <benjamin.walsh@windriver.com>
Date: Thu, 4 Dec 2008 17:06:01 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] EDAC: add check for interrupt state in init

Add interrupt as a valid operational state in addition to NMI and
poll mode.

Signed-off by: Benjamin Walsh <benjamin.walsh@windriver.com>
---
 include/linux/edac.h |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/include/linux/edac.h b/include/linux/edac.h
index 7cf92e8..8be109d 100644
--- a/include/linux/edac.h
+++ b/include/linux/edac.h
@@ -31,6 +31,7 @@ static inline void opstate_init(void)
 	switch (edac_op_state) {
 	case EDAC_OPSTATE_POLL:
 	case EDAC_OPSTATE_NMI:
+	case EDAC_OPSTATE_INT:
 		break;
 	default:
 		edac_op_state = EDAC_OPSTATE_POLL;
